00:03:14.100 --> 00:03:18.310
The book I've been asked to talk
about, the African Imagination

00:03:18.310 --> 00:03:22.930 position:56%
In Music is an introduction to black
African music published last year

00:03:22.930 --> 00:03:27.350
by Oxford University press, here
is what I say on the opening page

00:03:27.350 --> 00:03:30.430
of the introduction quote.

00:03:30.430 --> 00:03:35.150
"In its richness and diversity
Africa music remains one

00:03:35.150 --> 00:03:38.060
of the most vital repertories
performed today.

00:03:38.060 --> 00:03:41.780
It's history reaches back
into the ancient times,

00:03:41.780 --> 00:03:46.060
its continued cultivation
on the continent is as alive

00:03:46.060 --> 00:03:49.280
