00:20:17.960 --> 00:20:22.210
So let me set idealism aside,
I always find it convenient

00:20:22.210 --> 00:20:26.230
to do that, and do what's
doable in the 30 minutes

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:30.750
or so that I have left and I'm just
going to identify four principles,

00:20:30.750 --> 00:20:33.360
or concept that I consider
fundamental

00:20:33.360 --> 00:20:34.960
to African rhythmic expression.

00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:38.650
First is the distinction between
rhythms of speech and rhythms

00:20:38.650 --> 00:20:42.050
of the body, second is polyrhythm,

00:20:42.050 --> 00:20:45.530
third is the so-called
timeline pattern,

00:20:45.530 --> 00:20:50.300
and fourth are the master
drummer's rhythmic narratives.

00:20:50.300 --> 00:20:53.650
So my interest here is
in the foundations rather

00:20:53.650 --> 00:20:56.650
than their decorative
exterior, the base if you

00:20:56.650 --> 00:20:59.260 position:56%
like rather than the superstructure.

00:20:59.260 --> 00:21:01.530
I suggest that the complexity

00:21:01.530 --> 00:21:06.030
of African rhythm the so-called
complexity is an orderly

00:21:06.030 --> 00:21:10.780
and rational complexity not
the outcome of happenstance

00:21:10.780 --> 00:21:14.490
or a vaguely defined
improvisory [phonetics] process.

00:21:14.490 --> 00:21:18.480
By attending to its structural
aspects through analysis,

00:21:18.480 --> 00:21:22.600
we can appreciate better the
real intellectual achievements

00:21:22.600 --> 00:21:25.860
of African musicians.

00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:29.540
So first rhythms of speech
and rhythms of the body.

00:21:29.540 --> 00:21:32.840
So the world of rhythm
is made up of two kinds,

00:21:32.840 --> 00:21:35.190
rhythms of speech,
and rhythms the body.

00:21:35.190 --> 00:21:39.370
Rhythms of speech are that
gyrational, accentual,

00:21:39.370 --> 00:21:43.150
and periodic patterns
that result from speech

00:21:43.150 --> 00:21:47.410
in everyday verbal communication,
syllabic durations alternate

00:21:47.410 --> 00:21:51.720
between long and short,
accentual patterns emerge either

00:21:51.720 --> 00:21:54.730
from phenomenal stress
associated with timbre

00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:58.630
or from tonal change
while periodicity is says

00:21:58.630 --> 00:22:02.870
in the asymmetrical successional
segments of performed speech.

00:22:02.870 --> 00:22:07.990 position:56%
Be it a greeting, the swearing of an
oath, a town crier's announcement,

00:22:07.990 --> 00:22:10.920
the pouring of libation,
the minister's sermon,

00:22:10.920 --> 00:22:15.000
a radio announcer's interview,
the Chiefs linguists admonition,

00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:18.380
or a traditional healers
incantations.

00:22:18.380 --> 00:22:21.910
The rhythms of spoken language
may be reproduced directly

00:22:21.910 --> 00:22:24.570
in a speech mode of
instrumental performance

00:22:24.570 --> 00:22:27.870
or incorporated into song.

00:22:27.870 --> 00:22:34.100 position:56%
Rhythms of the body are showcased in
the scores of dances performed daily

00:22:34.100 --> 00:22:38.890
across the continent [inaudible]
in Uganda, Kpanlogo in Ghana,

00:22:38.890 --> 00:22:42.920
Nganda in Gambia, [inaudible] in
Cameroun, Sindimba [phonetics]

00:22:42.920 --> 00:22:46.480
in Tanzania, [inaudible]
in Nigeria and so on.

00:22:46.480 --> 00:22:52.870
These repetitive rhythms enable,
motivate or accompany movements,

00:22:52.870 --> 00:22:57.060
whereas rhythms of the body are
modes of communal expression,

00:22:57.060 --> 00:23:00.910
rhythms of speech are modes
of individual expression,

00:23:00.910 --> 00:23:04.300
whenever speech takes on
a mode of communality,

00:23:04.300 --> 00:23:10.350
it submits to regulation and
is molded into poetry or song.

00:23:10.350 --> 00:23:14.280
The rhythms of the body then act
closer to music than to speech

00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:17.820
because their purpose is
to carve time in response

00:23:17.820 --> 00:23:21.520
to movements while rhythms
of the body have the capacity

00:23:21.520 --> 00:23:23.660
to communicate verbal messages,

00:23:23.660 --> 00:23:28.040
their primary purpose is
to make play possible.

00:23:28.040 --> 00:23:32.610
Now distinguishing the
rhythms of speech from those

00:23:32.610 --> 00:23:36.200
of the body allows us to
present their conjunction

00:23:36.200 --> 00:23:41.760
as a basic syntactical
unit in African performers.

00:23:41.760 --> 00:23:47.170
A favorite organizational device is
the succession speech mode followed

00:23:47.170 --> 00:23:50.800
by song mode where song may
include dance which serves

00:23:50.800 --> 00:23:54.190
